<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de aplicar técnicas de trabajo colaborativo en equipos multidisciplinares y liderazgo, así como utilizar métodos para asumir la responsabilidad de orientar y realizar trabajos científicos en el ámbito de la Inteligencia Artificial. (To be able to apply collaborative work techniques in multidisciplinary teams and leadership, as well as use methods to take responsibility for guiding and carrying out scientific work in the field of Artificial Intelligence). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C2> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C2" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de analizar y evaluar los problemas éticos y sociales relacionados con la Inteligencia Artificial, y tener la capacidad de aplicar la teoría a casos prácticos relevantes. (To be able to analyze and evaluate ethical and social problems related to Artificial Intelligence, and have the ability to apply theory to relevant practical cases). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C3> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C3" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de concebir, desarrollar y validar nuevos sistemas que puedan aumentar la calidad de vida de las personas, y realizar, en contextos académicos y profesionales, innovaciones o avances tecnológicos que puedan hacer avanzar el estado del arte en áreas relacionadas con la Inteligencia Artificial. (To be able to conceive, develop, and validate new systems that can improve people's quality of life, and carry out, in academic and professional contexts, innovations or technological advances that can advance the state of the art in areas related to Artificial Intelligence). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C4> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C4" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de resolver problemas e integrar conocimiento en temas nuevos o escasamente definidos y en entornos multidisciplinares del área de la Inteligencia Artificial. (To be able to solve problems and integrate knowledge in new or loosely defined topics and multidisciplinary environments in the field of Artificial Intelligence). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C6> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C6" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de aplicar metodologías, procedimientos, herramientas y normas del estado del arte para la creación de nuevos componentes tecnológicos. (To be able to apply methodologies, procedures, tools, and standards from the state of the art for the creation of new technological components). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C7> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C7" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de construir nuevas hipótesis y modelos, evaluarlos y aplicarlos a la resolución de problemas en el área de la Inteligencia Artificial. (To be able to build new hypotheses and models, evaluate them, and apply them to problem"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de explicar e interpretar adecuadamente los resultados de la modelización y análisis de datos proporcionados por las técnicas de Inteligencia Artificial, utilizando plataformas existentes. (To be able to properly explain and interpret the results of modeling and data analysis provided by Artificial Intelligence techniques, using existing platforms). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/C9> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C9" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Tener la capacidad de evaluar la aplicación de los algoritmos de Inteligencia Artificial, sus ventajas y limitaciones, y de seleccionar adecuadamente las técnicas apropiadas para un problema práctico o de investigación. (To have the ability to evaluate the application of Artificial Intelligence algorithms, their advantages and limitations, and to appropriately select the techniques suitable for a practical or research problem). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los fundamentos de la investigación y la gestión de proyectos en el campo de la Inteligencia Artificial, las oportunidades y los riesgos, así como las implicaciones éticas, sociales y legales. (To understand the fundamentals of research and project management in the field of Artificial Intelligence, including opportunities, risks, and ethical, social, and legal implications). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K2> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K2" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los modelos cuantitativos que dan soporte a los procesos de toma de decisiones en sus distintas variantes. (To understand quantitative models that support decision"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K3> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K3" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer la teoría, los algoritmos y las herramientas software del aprendizaje automático. (To understand the theory, algorithms, and software tools of machine learning). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K4> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K4" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer las principales técnicas de computación natural, tanto a nivel simbólico como físico, e identificar su idoneidad para distintos tipos de problemas. (To understand the main techniques of natural computing, both at a symbolic and physical level, and identify their suitability for different types of problems). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los métodos de representación del conocimiento y razonamiento aplicables al desarrollo de sistemas inteligentes en entornos centralizados y distribuidos. (To understand the methods of knowledge representation and reasoning applicable to the development of intelligent systems in centralized and distributed environaments). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K6> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K6" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los problemas relacionados con la robótica y la visión por computador, y los algoritmos que los resuelven. (To understand the problems related to robotics and computer vision, and the algorithms that solve them). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/K7> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K7" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los avances más recientes en el ámbito de la Inteligencia Artificial. (To understand the latest advances in the field of Artificial Intelligence). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/RA115> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA115" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Los resultados del aprendizaje correspondientes a esta asignatura han quedado definidos en el apartado de competencias de este documento, señalando los que corresponden a conocimientos, habilidades y competencias propiamente dichas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Plantear un proyecto de investigación, teniendo en cuenta los riesgos y los aspectos éticos, sociales y legales. (To formulate a research project, considering risks and ethical, social, and legal aspects). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S2> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S2" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Aplicar los modelos cuantitativos que dan soporte a los procesos de toma de decisiones en sus distintas variantes. (To know how to apply quantitative models that support decision"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S3> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S3" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Analizar conjuntos de datos para identificar propiedades generales o relaciones que permitan explicar unos datos a partir de otros, aplicar algoritmos de aprendizaje automático para generar automáticamente modelos a partir de dichos datos y evaluar el rendimiento de dichos modelos. (To analyze data sets to identify general properties or relationships that explain one data set from another, apply machine learning algorithms to automatically generate models from such data, and evaluate the performance of such models). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S4> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S4" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Aplicar las principales técnicas de computación natural, tanto a nivel simbólico como físico, en base a su idoneidad para distintos tipos de problemas. (To apply the main techniques of natural computing, both at a symbolic and physical level, based on their suitability for different types of problems). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Almacenar conocimiento de forma que sea procesable por sistemas informáticos, posibilitando su reutilización en diferentes aplicaciones, y construir sistemas con capacidades de razonamiento para realizar de forma automática tareas tales como planificación o análisis de consistencia. (To store knowledge in a way that is processable by computer systems, enabling its reuse in different applications, and build systems with reasoning capabilities to automatically perform tasks such as planning or consistency analysis). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S6> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S6" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Analizar un problema de robótica o de visión por computador, determinar qué técnica es la más adecuada para su resolución y evaluar su funcionamiento. (To analyze a problem in robotics or computer vision, determine which technique is most suitable for its resolution, and evaluate its performance). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S7> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S7" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Aplicar de manera efectiva y avanzada las técnicas de Inteligencia Artificial en contextos complejos y en constante evolución. (To effectively and advancedly apply Artificial Intelligence techniques in complex and constantly evolving contexts). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/S8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Identificar áreas de aplicación en las que se puedan utilizar las técnicas y métodos de la Inteligencia Artificial y aplicar los mismos de manera adecuada. (To identify application areas where Artificial Intelligence techniques and methods can be used and apply them appropriately). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000372/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The final grade of this class is computed from the grades obtained in each of the six seminars taken.
If all the grades are at least 5 out of 10, then the final grade will be the average of the six. Otherwise, the final grade will be the minimum of the six.

The student obtains his or her grades during the semester, as long as the seminars take place.

In both the ordinary period (convocatoria ordinaria) and the extraordinary period (convocatoria extraordinaria), the student who hasn't passed the class (because he or she did not obtain at least 5 out of 10 in six seminars during the teaching period) can take suitable evaluation activities of one or more seminars. Such activities will be decided by the teachers of each seminar and will allow the student to pass the class.

The evaluation activities in each one of them vary, being those indicated below:

S1: Research methodology: Although the seminar is compulsory, attendance is not mandatory. The student will individually do a test and perform a work:
Test related to the contents of the seminar, done at the end of the seminar (30%).
Summarizing the most important points addressed in the seminar (70%).
S2: Project management and risk analysis: The final grade is obtained as follows:
Grade of written summary of the most important points presented at the seminar (30%).
Grade of written summary and presentation of one of the topics presented in class (30%).
Grade of attendance and participation in class (40%). The student must attend at least the 80% of the classes.
S3: Ethical and legal aspects of Artificial Intelligence: The final grade is obtained as follows:
Two Moodle questionnaires made during the sessions 2 and 3 and one paper questionnaire during the last session. The evaluation is obtained as the average of these questionnaires.
Attendance is strongly recommended.
S4: Artificial Intelligence and Inclusion:
Students will have to deliver an individual report around a topic proposed during the seminar where all the skills acquired in this course are demonstrated.
Attendance and participation during the sessions could be also considered.
S5: Decision Analysis:
Regular attendance to class will be an essential condition.
Individual summary about the theoretical content of the course. It will be evaluated according to its completeness, clarity and coherence.
Collective work on the state of the art of the discipline through a specific wiki associated to the seminar. It will be evaluated according to the participation index, the ability to interconnect ideas, clarity and originality.
S6: Machine Learning:
Attendance will be mandatory.
The student will individually perform a practical work consisting of software management and oral presentation of an application case.
S7: Natural computing:
Compulsory attendance at the seminars (35%).
Individual work summary report (65%).
S8: Knowledge representation and reasoning: The final grade will be computed in the following way:
Attendance to the classes (40%)
Written test about the topics covered in the seminar (60%).
S9: Fuzzy logic:
Attendance to the classes (40%).
There will be a written exam on the last day of the seminar, without the possibility of consulting notes, bibliography or any other type of documentation (60%).
S10: Cognitive computing:
Attendance to class (a minimum of 80% attendance is mandatory) (40%).
Summary of the most important points discussed in the seminar. The clarity, coherence and correct use of the terminology will be evaluated (30%).
Individual work that delves into one of the topics covered in the seminar. The presentation, clarity and adequacy of the bibliography will be evaluated (30%).
S11: Cognitive robotics and perception:
Attendance and participation in classes during the seminar (15%).
Practical project, including its presentation and defense (85%).
S12: Principles of robotic locomotion:
Attendance and participation in classes during the seminar (25%).
Practical project (75%).
S13: Application of Artificial Intelligence:
Attendance of the students to the seminar.
The development of a practical work on one of the topics of the seminar. The workload necessary for this practice will be adequate and proportional to the idea of a seminar and the number of credits.
S14: Natural Language processing:
Attendance in at least 80% of the classes.
A work done individually or in a group on a topic to be defined related to the exploration of information on some type of system in the market, its analysis and conclusions. It is not intended with this work more than to accustom the student to search existing solutions in the market and learn to develop an idea of how to solve them. The qualification in the extraordinary period will be governed by the same rules as in the ordinary one. Attendance 80% of the classes is required as well as to delivery an individual or group work.
S15: Automated planning:
Attendance to the classes and short practices carried out during the seminar (50%).
A project that will be carried out by the students (50%).
S16: Generative AI: Applications ad Challenges:
Attendance of the students to the seminar.
Peer assessment among students.
The development of a practical work on one of the topics of the seminar. The workload necessary for this practice will be adequate and proportional to the idea of a seminar and the number of credits.
[ Global and extraordinary assessment ] : This may include a written exam, and the practical project may differ from the one carried out during the ordinary assessment. In all cases, the evaluation will take place face to face.
Seminars by visiting professors:
The evaluation activities of these seminars will be established by the visiting teachers.
Attending one or more of these seminars may be awarded with a bonus of up to +1.0 points on the total grade of the whole subject (i.e., is the average grade of the six seminars is 7.7, the student could get a maximum of 8.7 as the final grade), with the condition that such total grade is already at least 5 out of 10. The subject coordinator will decide how to apply the bonus, taking into account the specific circumstances (number of seminars, numbers of sessions in each seminar, etc.). The bonus is not meant to be taken for granted by the students, who will be informed in due time about if and how the bonus will be given."""@es ;
